@node "whatis_e" "VideoArchiv v3.0 (English)"
@prev "main"
@next "news_e"

@{b}What is VideoArchiv@{ub}
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

@{b}The idea behind VideoArchiv:@{ub}

The idea behind VideoArchiv  was to create a simple, but  powerful  video-
database. It was  never our  goal  to develop  a  programme  that would do
everything, but we think that this version is pretty close!
@{b}VideoArchiv wants to  be the clearest, most comprehensible  and easiest to
use video-database for the Amiga@{ub}. It is hoped  that everyone will  be able
to use this programme easily. Programmes are already available that strike
you  dead  with  masks, requiring  complicated  setups, that  need  to  be
arduously edited by the user. Anyone who wants to manage their collections
of videos needs a programme which is specialized for videos;
here is VideoArchiv :-)

@{b}Features of VideoArchiv v3.0:@{ub}
  - Easy to use.
  - Powerful search options.
  - Powerful print options.
  - Seperate Genre, Director and Actor lists.
  - Ability to record any loaned video.
  - Various, multiple sort options.
  - Locale under OS >2.04; German and Swedish catalogue included.
  - Nice GUI.
  - Install script included (Commodore installer used).
  - English and German documentation included.

@endnode



@node "news_e" "News in VideoArchiv v3.0"
@prev "whatis_e"
@next "licence_e"

                                 @{b}HISTORY@{ub}
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

@{b}VideoArchiv v3.0@{ub}
----------------

Release Date: 20.11.1997

New for Version 3.0:

  - revised the layout of  the programme. Logos  redrawn so  now they  use
    less space. Title-bar added  to all windows. Double  borders to  split
    screens by topics, and to help navigate through the programme.

  - palette colours  are allocated  singularly to make it easier  to adapt
    them individualy.

  - enhanced layout functions;- now more powerful and much faster.

  - increased speed while  scrolling in any listview, while  pressing  the
    mouse button.

  - new fields added to the edit mask:
    - original title.
    - year.
    - language.
    - option to add the year.
    - sound format.
    - screen format.
    - medium.
    All fields  are voluntary. It is  now possible to set standards, which
    will be displayed whenever a new film is added.
    Because  these  fields  were  unavailable  in  previous  versions, the
    standard values can now be used to fill in the gaps.

  - easy to use load, and save, requesters; allowing the user to save many
    different video lists, under different names.

  - powerful  print machine; now allows easy editing of  the layout in any
    print outs.

  - enhanced search options; now  able to  search  using, SP/LP, language,
    status, age, sound, format, and medium. New  options: search  from the
    current position, and now also case sensitive.

  - search results can be displayed in two ways:
    1. as in previous "search  by step" versions, each  film matching  the
       search parameters is shown in it's own window. A simple mouse click
       will show the  next  search result (more data is now displayed than
       in any previous versions).
    2. all films  matching the  search parameters  are shown together in a
       lister window for  a good overview. From here  the results  can  be
       printed or edited with a double click.

  - new options for the setup screen:
    - enable/disable automatic backup.
    - show a record, or  move to the edit screen, when the mouse is double
      clicked.
    - set default values.
    - edit a default load or save path.
    - enter the name of the VA file to be loaded at startup.

  - more data will be shown if a double click is made on any film shown on
    the main screen.

  - file name now displayed at the top of the screen when editing.

  - status line, and progress bar; now shows the progress while searching,
    or when printing and sorting.

  - loaned  films are  now marked with a «+» symbol; a double  click  will
    show the name and the date of issuing.

  - ability to select more than  one list  option from the listview in the
    edit screen (genre, director or actor).

  - when adding numerous films, it is no longer necessary to return to the
    main screen each time to continue.

  - in every  listview «cursor right»  and «cursor left» can  be  used  to
    enable the next or previous record in that list.

  - bug fixed in the deleting routine.

  - real double click now used.

  - registration now without a keyfile (only a password required).



@{b}VideoArchiv v2.0@{ub}
----------------

Release Date: 01.05.96

New for Version 2.0:

  - locale library support. French and German catalogue included.

  - now able to edit  lists of genre, director and actor names. Frequently
    used names can now be selected easily from a listview.

  - enhanced sorting algorithms enables increased speed when sorting.

  - new file formats; allows the programmer to  build new features without
    loosing compatibility.

  - double clicking  on any  film in  the  mainscreen will  now  show  the
    recorded data in it's own window.

  - ability to delete the complete film list. Deletion must be confirmed.

  - backup automatically created.

  - search results can now be edited directly.

  - actual system date now shown in  the issuing window, in the respective
    fields.

  - listviewers  display  all  films  can now  be  scrolled  using «cursor
    right» or «cursor left» to enable the next or  previous record in each
    list.

  - all layout functions revised (now a lot faster).



@{b}VideoArchiv v1.2@{ub}
----------------

Release Date: 10.10.95

  First public release.



See @{"Licence" link licence_e 0} on how to register.

@endnode



